                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should a search warrant issued by a Judge of the District Court take?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Form 34.23, Part","Form 35.23, Schedule","Form 34.23, Schedule","Form 34.23, Schedule A"],"justification":"A search warrant issued by a Judge of the District Court on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.23](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/512484f3-93de-403a-b15a-d956d4037211/Search Warrant - Criminal Law Amendment Act, 1935 section 19 No. 34.23.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- Form of warrant.* (3) A search warrant issued by a Judge of the District Court on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.23](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/512484f3-93de-403a-b15a-d956d4037211/Search Warrant - Criminal Law Amendment Act, 1935 section 19 No. 34.23.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'To whom should an application for a warrant under the Child Trafficking and Pornography Act 1998 be made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["The Attorney General","The local magistrate or justice of the peace","The District Court Judge for the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated.","The Chief Justice of the Supreme Court"],"justification":"may be made to the District Court Judge for the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Application for,* 11.[7] (1) An application to the District Court for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 7 of the [Child Trafficking and Pornography Act 1998](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1998/act/22/enacted/en/html) may be made to the District Court Judge for the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'To whom can a member of the Garda Síochána apply for a search warrant under the European Arrest Warrant Act 2003?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["The Minister for Justice and Equality must approve the application before proceeding.","A member of the Garda Síochána must apply to the Chief Superintendent of their division.","A Judge of the District Court assigned to the district within which the dwelling concerned is situated.","A Justice of the High Court in the jurisdiction where the search will take place."],"justification":"An application to a judge of the District Court by a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section of the European Arrest Warrant Act 2003 may be made to a Judge of the District Court assigned to the district within which the dwelling concerned is situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - for purposes of the European Arrest Warrant Act 2003 (No. 45 of 2003) 15[9](1) An application to a judge of the District Court by a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section of the [European Arrest Warrant Act 2003](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2003/act/45) may be made to a Judge of the District Court assigned to the district within which the dwelling concerned is situated. (2). Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing in the Form [34.33](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/62eef001-c6c3-493a-8a77-9fefdacb4823/Information For Search Warrant - European Arrest Warrant Act 2003 section No. 34.33.docx/docx/1) Schedule of the member of the Garda Síochána applying for such warrant. (3) A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.34](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/ff8a8613-5fec-479d-ab1b-8eeba1a528f7/Search Warrant - European Arrest Warrant Act 2003 section No. 34.34.docx/docx/1) Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'To whom can an application for a warrant under section 50(4) of the Food Safety Authority of Ireland Act 1998 be made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["The Chief Justice of the Supreme Court for any district","The Minister for Health for the entire country","The Garda Síochána (Irish police force) Commissioner for the county where the premises is located","The Judge of the District Court for the District Court District wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated."],"justification":"An application to the District Court for the issue of a warrant pursuant to sub-section (4) of section 50 of the [Food Safety Authority of Ireland Act 1998](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1998/act/29) may be made to the Judge of the District Court for the District Court District wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *- under the Food Safety Authority of Ireland Act 1998* 16[10](1). An application to the District Court for the issue of a warrant pursuant to sub-section (4) of section 50 of the [Food Safety Authority of Ireland Act 1998](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1998/act/29) may be made to the Judge of the District Court for the District Court District wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. (2).Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing in the Form [34.35](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/63344470-d644-47ee-86c6-461529e205e0/Information For Issue Of Warrant - Food Safety Authority Of Ireland Act 1998 section 50(4) No. 34.35.docx/docx/1) Schedule of an authorised officer. A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.36](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/63344470-d644-47ee-86c6-461529e205e0/Information For Issue Of Warrant - Food Safety Authority Of Ireland Act 1998 section 50(4) No. 34.35.docx/docx/1) Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should the application for a warrant be made in?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Form 34.37","Form 3.43","Form 34.73","Form 43.37"],"justification":"Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.37](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/4d9d1b71-310c-4f5d-9d38-d24a5b571ad4/Information For Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1997, section 10(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 6(1)(A)) No. 34.37.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Criminal Justice (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1997 (No. 4 of 1997) as amended by the Criminal Justice Act 2006 (No. 26 of 2006) 17.[11] An application by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of sergeant for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 10(1) of the [Criminal Justice (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1997](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1997/act/4/enacted/en/html) (as substituted by section 6(1)(a) of the [Criminal Justice Act 2006](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2006/act/26/enacted/en/print.html)) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.37](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/4d9d1b71-310c-4f5d-9d38-d24a5b571ad4/Information For Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1997, section 10(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 6(1)(A)) No. 34.37.docx/docx/1), Schedule A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.38](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/33ce7aa2-489a-4684-bcbd-7a3eb5aef37c/Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1997, section 10(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 6(1)(a)) No. 34.38.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'To whom can a bureau officer apply for a warrant under section 14(1) of the Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["The Chief Superintendent of the Garda Síochána","The President of Ireland","The Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated.","The Minister for Justice"],"justification":"An application by a bureau officer who is a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 14(1) of the [Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1996/act/31/enacted/en/html) (as substituted by section 190(1) of the [Criminal Justice Act 2006](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2006/act/26/enacted/en/print.html)) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996 (No. 31 of 1996) as amended by the Criminal Justice Act 2006 (No. 26 of 2006) 18.[12] An application by a bureau officer who is a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 14(1) of the [Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1996/act/31/enacted/en/html) (as substituted by section 190(1) of the [Criminal Justice Act 2006](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2006/act/26/enacted/en/print.html)) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. Such application shall be by information on oath and in writing of such bureau officer in the Form [34.39](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/1a2857ba-9fd7-4209-b3fc-3e2661a8b9a7/Information For Search Warrant - Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996, section 14(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 190(1)) No. 34.39.docx/docx/1), Schedule A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.40](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/ef1ce8ff-3a86-4918-99bf-b293765e8399/Search Warrant - Criminal Assets Bureau Act 1996, section 14(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 190(1)) No. 34.40.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'To whom can a member of the Garda Síochána apply for a warrant under section 5 of the Prevention of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["The Chief Superintendent of the Garda Síochána assigned to the district in question.","The Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated.","The Minister for Justice and Equality of Ireland.","The President of Ireland."],"justification":"An application by a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 5 of the Prevention of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001 (as substituted by section 191(1) of the Criminal Justice Act 2006) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Prevention of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001 (No. 27 of 2001) as amended by the Criminal Justice Act 2006 (No. 26 of 2006) 19.[13] An application by a member of the Garda Síochána for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 5 of the [Prevention of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2001/act/27)(as substituted by section 191(1) of the Criminal Justice Act 2006) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. Such application shall be by information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.41](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/d6b525d4-771f-49f9-a131-38b00cede916/Information For Search Warrant - Prevention Of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001, section 5(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice Act 2006, section 191(1)) No. 34.41.docx/docx/1), Schedule A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.42](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/b584dbb0-b910-4871-8637-4f51062bef5f/Search Warrant - Prevention Of Corruption (Amendment) Act 2001, section 5(1) (as substituted by section 191(1) of the Criminal Justice Act 2006) No. 34.42.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'Who can apply for a warrant under the Consumer Protection Act 2007?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["A consumer who has been affected by unfair trade practices","An authorised officer appointed or continued in accordance with section 30 of the Consumer Protection Act 2007","A member of the local council where the alleged violation occurred","Any citizen of the country over the age of 18"],"justification":"An application by an authorised officer (for the time being appointed or continued as such in accordance with section 30 of the [Consumer Protection Act 2007](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2007/act/19) (No 19 of 2007) for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 30(10) of the said Act of 2007 may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought are situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Consumer Protection Act 2007 (No.19 of 2007) 20.[14] An application by an authorised officer (for the time being appointed or continued as such in accordance with section 30 of the [Consumer Protection Act 2007](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2007/act/19) (No 19 of 2007) for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 30(10) of the said Act of 2007 may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought are situated. Such application shall be by sworn information in writing of such authorised officer in the Form [34.43](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/97eb138f-2653-42ab-92c1-5ad5fe8343e8/Information for search warrant - Consumer Protection Act 2007, section 30(10) No. 34.43.docx/docx/1), Schedule A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.44](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/5feff534-1bd9-460d-86b5-202ae0601cd6/Search Warrant - Consumer Protection Act 2007, section 30(10) No. 34.44.docx/docx/1), Schedule 21.[15] (1) An application pursuant to section 74(7) of the [Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/act/7/enacted/en/html) by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of inspector for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 74(8) of the said Act may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District where the place concerned is situated, by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.45](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/45736e09-2c8e-4386-a391-3ec7afb4e7c1/Information for warrant - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 74(7) No. 34.45.docx/docx/1), Schedule A warrant granted on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.46](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/63d5bbb7-4820-4632-b931-835034d315cc/Search warrant - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 74(7) No. 34.46.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form does a member of the Garda Síochána use when applying for an order under section 75(10)(a) of the Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Form 34.46","Form 34.48","Form 34.47","Form 27.47"],"justification":"the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.47](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/8ea7a75b-2368-42bf-85b7-a83e73c72b4a/Information - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 75(8) No. 34.47.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '(2) An application under section 75(8) of the said Act of 2008 by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of inspector for an order under section 75(10)(a) of the said Act of 2008 that a person produce evidential material to a named member of the Garda Síochána so that he or she may take it away, or give such member access to it, and/or for an order under section of the said Act to require any person who appears to the Judge to be entitled to grant entry to the place to allow the member to enter it to obtain access to the material may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the evidential material is situated by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.47](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/8ea7a75b-2368-42bf-85b7-a83e73c72b4a/Information - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 75(8) No. 34.47.docx/docx/1), Schedule An application by a member of the Garda Síochána for an order under section of the said Act of 2008 may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the evidential material is situated by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.48](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/a7ab6e34-2902-447b-8720-696492cf19ea/Information for order under section only - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 75(8) No. 34.48.docx/docx/1), Schedule An order made under section 75(10) of the said Act of 2008 on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.49](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/4b99847a-72bd-499f-bda8-23e622245eb0/Order - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 75(10) No. 34.49.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'When must the original notice of application be lodged with the Clerk?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["not later than five days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application","not later than one day before the date fixed for the hearing of the application","not later than two days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application","on the same day as the hearing of the application"],"justification":"the original notice of application shall be lodged with the Clerk not later than two days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '(3) An application for an order under section 75(14) of the said Act of 2008 varying or discharging an order made under section 75(10) shall, unless the Judge otherwise permits, be preceded by the issue of a notice of application in the Form [34.50](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/3dfe4ae4-0adf-4a1f-bc14-ebcca08da8da/Notice of application to - vary - discharge an order under section 75(10) of the Act - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 75(14) No. 34.50.docx/docx/1), Schedule A copy of the notice of application shall be served upon the member of the Garda Síochána named in the order or the person to whom the order relates not later than four days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application, and the original notice of application shall be lodged with the Clerk not later than two days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application. The original order shall be produced in court on the hearing of any application for an order varying or discharging it. Any variation ordered may be endorsed on the original or a copy of the order and dated and signed by the Judge.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should be used when applying for an order under section 63(3)?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Form 34.51","Form 34.52","Form 34.50","Form 34"],"justification":"by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.51](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/2dd3b073-dd91-4a99-baf7-ab451a9ca82e/Information - Criminal Justice Act 1994, 63(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 105) No. 34.51.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under section 63 of the Criminal Justice Act 1994 (No. 15 of 1994)(as substituted by section of the [Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/act/7/enacted/en/html) 22.[16] (1) An application under section 63(1) of the [Criminal Justice Act 1994](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1994/act/15) by a member of the Garda Síochána for an order under section 63(3) of the said Act that a person produce material to a named member of the Garda Síochána so that he or she may take it away, or give such member access to it, may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the material is situated, by the information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.51](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/2dd3b073-dd91-4a99-baf7-ab451a9ca82e/Information - Criminal Justice Act 1994, 63(1) (as substituted by Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 105) No. 34.51.docx/docx/1), Schedule An order made on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.52](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/bb97df40-af32-4e2d-b8a9-a91f9ea06db3/Order - Criminal Justice Act 1994, 63(3) ( as substituted by Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, 105) No. 34.52.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should be issued for an application under section 63(7) of the Criminal Justice Act 1994?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Form 34.34","Form 35.53","Form 34.53","Form 27.53"],"justification":"An application under section 63(7) of the said Act for an order varying or discharging an order made under section 63(3) shall, unless the Judge otherwise permits, be preceded by the issue of a notice of application in the Form [34.53](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/1e36faca-9252-47ed-8409-cb91683ac51a/Notice%20of%20application%20to%20vary%20-%20discharge%20an%20order%20under%20section%2063(3)%20of%20the%20Act%20-%20Criminal%20Justice%20Act%201994,%20s.%2063(7)%20(as%20substituted%20by%20Criminal%20Justice%20(Mutual%20Assistance)%20Act%202008,%20s.105)%20No.%2034.53.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '(2) An application under section 63(7) of the said Act for an order varying or discharging an order made under section 63(3) shall, unless the Judge otherwise permits, be preceded by the issue of a notice of application in the Form [34.53](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/1e36faca-9252-47ed-8409-cb91683ac51a/Notice of application to vary - discharge an order under section 63(3) of the Act - Criminal Justice Act 1994, 63(7) (as substituted by Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008, No. 34.53.docx/docx/1), Schedule A copy of the notice of application shall be served upon the member of the Garda Síochána named in the order or the person to whom the order relates not later than four days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application, and the original notice of application shall be lodged with the Clerk not later than two days before the date fixed for the hearing of the application. The original order shall be produced in court on the hearing of any application for an order varying or discharging it. Any variation ordered may be endorsed on the original or a copy of the order and dated and signed by the Judge'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should the application for a warrant under section 12(4) take?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["It should be by verbal testimony in front of a judge.","It should be submitted anonymously without any formal documentation.","It should be a signed affidavit on Form 34.53, Schedule A.","It should be by information on oath and in writing in the Form 34.54, Schedule"],"justification":"Such application shall be by information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.54](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/99ea917b-d3f8-4022-9701-482218aa40bb/Information for Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Psychoactive Substances) Act 2010 section 12(4) No. 34.54.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## -under section 12(4) of the Criminal Justice (Psychoactive Substances) Act 2010 (No. 22 of 2010) 23. [17] An application by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of sergeant for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 12(4) of the [Criminal Justice (Psychoactive Substances) Act 2010](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2010/act/22) may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the dwelling in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. Such application shall be by information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.54](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/99ea917b-d3f8-4022-9701-482218aa40bb/Information for Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Psychoactive Substances) Act 2010 section 12(4) No. 34.54.docx/docx/1), Schedule and shall be made and heard in accordance with [Order 12]([f669d9a7-009d-4d83-ddaa-000000000002|lng:en]59D3A380-82AD-48F7-9B9E-F3A4D928E077?url Order-12-District-Miscellaneous-Provisions), rule 27. A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.55](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/5439ad22-b5df-40ea-9a49-9f77edccada7/Search Warrant - Criminal Justice (Psychoactive Substances) Act 2010 section 12(4) No. 34.55.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'What form should the application be made in?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["Form 35.46","Form 34.65","Form 54.32","Form 34.56"],"justification":"in the Form [34.56](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/d7e5b3f1-de4e-4b52-8232-fd135a44a6e1/Information - Criminal Procedure Act 2010, section 18(2) No. 34.56.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Criminal Procedure Act 2010 24.[18] An application pursuant to section 18(2) of the [Criminal Procedure Act 2010](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2010/act/27/enacted/en/html) by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of superintendent for the issue of a warrant may be made to the Judge of the District Court assigned to the District Court District wherein the place in respect of which the warrant is sought is situated. Such application shall be by information on oath and in writing of such member in the Form [34.56](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/d7e5b3f1-de4e-4b52-8232-fd135a44a6e1/Information - Criminal Procedure Act 2010, section 18(2) No. 34.56.docx/docx/1), Schedule and shall be made and heard in accordance with [Order 12]([f669d9a7-009d-4d83-ddaa-000000000002|lng:en]59D3A380-82AD-48F7-9B9E-F3A4D928E077?url Order-12-District-Miscellaneous-Provisions), rule 27. A warrant issued on foot of such information shall be in the Form [34.57](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/afe6a1ec-b076-4dc1-b81a-8d5fb94cef7f/Search Warrant - Criminal Procedure Act 2010, section 18(2) No. 34.57.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'When was Order 34 rule 16 inserted?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["15 November 2004","14 November 2004","13 November 2004","14 December 2004"],"justification":"effective 14 November 2004"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '[10] Order 34 rule 16 inserted by [S.I. 700 of 2004](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2004/si/700/made/en/print?q 700&years 2004), effective 14 November 2004 [11] Order 34 rule 17 inserted by [S.I. 322 of 2008](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/si/322/made/en/print?q 322&years 2008), effective 8 September 2008 [12] Order 34 rule 18 inserted by [S.I. 322 of 2008](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/si/322/made/en/print?q 322&years 2008), effective 8 September 2008 [13] Order 34 rule 19 inserted by [S.I. 322 of 2008](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/si/322/made/en/print?q 322&years 2008), effective 8 September 2008 [14] Order 34 rule 20 inserted by [S.I. 106 of 2009](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2009/si/106/made/en/print?q 106&years 2009), effective 24 April 2009 [15] Order 34 rule 21 inserted by [S.I. 94 of 2010](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2010/si/94/made/en/print?q 94&years 2010), effective 5 April 2010 [16] Order 34 rule 22 inserted by [S.I. 94 of 2010](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2010/si/94/made/en/print?q 94&years 2010), effective 5 April 2010 [17] Order 34 rule 23 inserted by [S.I. 536 of 2011](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2011/si/536/made/en/print?q 536&years 2011), effective 11 November 2011 [18] Order 34 rule 24 inserted by [S.I. 585 of 2011](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2011/si/585/made/en/print?q 585&years 2011), effective 10 December 2011 [19] Order 34 rule 25 inserted by [S.I. 653 of 2011](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2011/si/653/made/en/print?q 653&years 2011), effective 4 January 2012'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34A - Criminal Justice (Surveillance) Act 2009', 'Court Rules', 'How is an application for continuing surveillance made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["In writing, without the need for an oath, and using Form 34A.10, 34A.11, or 34A.12.","Orally, in person, and using Form or","On oath, in writing, and using Form 34A.13, 34A.14, or 34A.15.","On oath, via email, and using Form 34A.16, 34A.17, or 34A.18."],"justification":"An application mentioned in subsection (10) of section 7 of the Act under subsection (4) of section 4 of the Act by the superior officer to a Judge of the District Court for an authorisation to continue the surveillance approved by the Superior Officer under subsection (3) of section 7 of the Act shall be made on oath and in writing of the applicant and in the Form [34A.13](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/d8f1bdd9-080a-4c02-836e-602aafe91e32/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - CriminalJustice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.13.docx/docx/1), [34A.14](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/e13a7ec9-22da-4846-8940-100dfac28819/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - Criminal Justice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.14.docx/docx/1), or [34A.15](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/5515aa13-dabc-4885-a9f9-3bbe7920265a/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - Criminal Justice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.15.docx/docx/1), as the case may be."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '(6) An application mentioned in subsection (10) of section 7 of the Act under subsection (4) of section 4 of the Act by the superior officer to a Judge of the District Court for an authorisation to continue the surveillance approved by the Superior Officer under subsection (3) of section 7 of the Act shall be made on oath and in writing of the applicant and in the Form [34A.13](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/d8f1bdd9-080a-4c02-836e-602aafe91e32/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - CriminalJustice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.13.docx/docx/1), [34A.14](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/e13a7ec9-22da-4846-8940-100dfac28819/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - Criminal Justice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.14.docx/docx/1), or [34A.15](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/5515aa13-dabc-4885-a9f9-3bbe7920265a/Information for an authorisation to continue surveillance - Criminal Justice (Surveillance) Act 2009, section 4(4) and section 7(10) No. 34A.15.docx/docx/1), as the case may be. (7) Applications to which this Order applies shall be made parte and otherwise than in public and may be made in chambers. [1] Order 34A inserted by [S.I. 314 of 2010](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2010/si/314/made/en/print?q 314&years 2010), effective 22 July 2010'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 35 - Certified Copies Of Orders And Of Other Documents', 'Court Rules', 'Who can sign an order recording a decision of a Judge of the District Court?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["A Judge or a County Clerk assigned to any County Court regardless of the specific District Court area where the order was made.","A notary public who is registered in the state where the District Court is located.","Any attorney involved in the case, provided they have been granted special permission by the presiding Judge.","A Judge or a District Court Clerk assigned to the District Court area in which the order was made, provided it complies with certain requirements."],"justification":"an order recording a decision of a Judge of the District Court may be signed by a Judge or (provided that it complies with the requirements of sub-rule (2)) by any District Court Clerk assigned to the District Court area in which the order was made."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '# Order 35 - Certified Copies Of Orders And Of Other Documents - Court: District 1.[1] (1) To the extent that sections 14(1) and 14(2) of the [Courts Act 1971](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1971/act/36/enacted/en/html) (as substituted by section 23 of the [Civil Law (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 2008](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/act/14)) provide that an order so signed shall be evidence in any legal proceedings of the said decision, an order recording a decision of a Judge of the District Court may be signed by a Judge or (provided that it complies with the requirements of sub-rule (2)) by any District Court Clerk assigned to the District Court area in which the order was made. (2)[2] When any order referred to in sub-rule (1) is intended to be signed by a District Court Clerk, the form of order shall: - immediately following the heading of the order, include the words “BY ORDER OF JUDGE ................................. a Judge of the District Court” and identify by name the Judge who made the order; - in the body of the order, recite the making of the order by that Judge, and - (iii) where a form of such order which may be signed by a Judge is included in any Schedule to these Rules: - (a) immediately following the place for signature, instead of the specification “Judge of the District Court” include the specification: “District Court Clerk assigned to the said District Court area”, and - contain such other modifications as are necessary. (3) To the extent that sections 14(3) and 14(4) of the Courts Act 1971 (as substituted by section 23 of the Civil Law (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 2008) provide that a warrant so signed shall be evidence in any legal proceedings of the matters to which the warrant relates, a warrant issued by a Judge of the District Court may be signed by a Judge or (provided that it complies with the requirements of sub-rule (4)) by any District Court Clerk assigned to the District Court area in which the warrant was issued.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 35 - Certified Copies Of Orders And Of Other Documents', 'Court Rules', 'Under what circumstances can a Judge direct the Clerk to provide a copy of an order or document?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["When a Judge is requested by a family member of one of the parties involved in the case.","When a Judge receives a formal request from a journalist for reporting purposes.","When a Judge is satisfied that a copy is reasonably required by any person for the purpose of legal proceedings.","When a Judge deems it necessary for the personal use of one of the attorneys involved."],"justification":"Where a Judge is satisfied that a copy of an order or other document is reasonably required by any person for the purpose of any legal proceedings, such Judge may direct the Clerk to furnish a copy of such order or other document to such person upon payment by such person of the prescribed fee (if any)."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '3. Where a Judge is satisfied that a copy of an order or other document is reasonably required by any person for the purpose of any legal proceedings, such Judge may direct the Clerk to furnish a copy of such order or other document to such person upon payment by such person of the prescribed fee (if any). 4. A copy of an order or other document furnished under this Order shall be certified by the Clerk to be a true copy of the original order or document as the case may be, which is in his or her custody. [1] Order 35, rule 1 substituted by [S.I. 92 of 2009](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2009/si/92/made/en/print?q 92&years 2009), effective 23 March 2009 [2] Order 25 sub rule (2) of rule 1 originally amended by [S.I. 41 of 1998](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1998/si/41/made/en/print?q 41&years 1998), substituted by [S.I. 92 of 2009](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2009/si/92/made/en/print?q 92&years 2009), effective 23 March 2009'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 36 - Costs And Witnesses'' Expenses', 'Court Rules', 'In which court does Order 36 apply?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["County Court","Supreme Court","District Court","High Court"],"justification":"- Court: District"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '# Order 36 - Costs And Witnesses'' Expenses - Court: District'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 36 - Costs And Witnesses'' Expenses', 'Court Rules', 'What power does the court have when making an order in a summary jurisdiction case?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["The court may order any party to serve jail time as it deems fit.","The court may order any party to pay a fine equivalent to the value of the claim as it deems fit.","The court may order any party to pay costs and witnesses'' expenses to the other party as it deems fit.","The court may order any party to provide community service as it deems fit."],"justification":"it may make an order in accordance with law ordering any party to the proceedings to pay to the other party such costs and witnesses’ expenses as it shall think fit to award."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *Costs in summary cases* 1.[[1]](#_ftn1) Where the Court makes an order in any case of summary jurisdiction (including an order to “strike out” for want of jurisdiction) it may make an order in accordance with law ordering any party to the proceedings to pay to the other party such costs and witnesses’ expenses as it shall think fit to award.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 36 - Costs And Witnesses'' Expenses', 'Court Rules', 'How are costs or witnesses'' expenses enforced if there is no provision in the Rules?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["They may be recovered through a court injunction.","They may be recovered by filing a separate civil lawsuit.","They may be recovered by automatic deduction from the defendant''s wages.","They may be recovered by warrant of distress."],"justification":"Where there is no provision in these Rules for the enforcement of an order awarding costs or witnesses'' expenses, such costs or expenses may be recovered by warrant of distress."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *Enforcement of order* 4. Where there is no provision in these Rules for the enforcement of an order awarding costs or witnesses'' expenses, such costs or expenses may be recovered by warrant of distress. [1]Order 36 rule 1 substituted by 496 of 2020](http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2020/si/496/made/en/print), effective 10 November 2020.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'Which individuals are allowed to attend the Children Court?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Any person over the age of 18, including tourists and visitors with no connection to the case","Children under the age of 16, as long as they are related to the case in some way","Officers of the court, parents or guardians of the child, adult relatives, persons directly involved in the proceedings, bona fide press representatives, and others permitted by the court''s discretion.","Individuals who have been previously convicted of a felony, provided they are not directly involved in the case"],"justification":"all persons shall be excluded from sittings of the Children Court except – - (a) officers of the court - the parents or guardian of the child concerned, - an adult relative to the child, or other adult who attends the court pursuant to section 91 (6) of the Act, - persons directly concerned in the proceedings, - bona fide representatives of the press, - such other persons (if any) as the court may at its discretion permit to remain."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '5. Subject to the Act and the preceding rules of this Order, the provisions of the Summary Jurisdiction Rules, 1909 (S.R. & 952) dated July 31, 1909 made under section 133(7) of the [Children Act, 1908](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1928/sro/8/made/en/print) shall, by operation of section 5 (1) of the Children Act, 2001, with any necessary modifications, apply to proceedings under the Act. 6. Notwithstanding any provision of [Order 14]([f669d9a7-009d-4d83-ddaa-000000000002|lng:en]59D3A380-82AD-48F7-9B9E-F3A4D928E077?url Order-14-District-Admission-To-Court-And-Publication-Of-Proceedings), all persons shall be excluded from sittings of the Children Court except – - (a) officers of the court - the parents or guardian of the child concerned, - an adult relative to the child, or other adult who attends the court pursuant to section 91 (6) of the Act, - persons directly concerned in the proceedings, - bona fide representatives of the press, - such other persons (if any) as the court may at its discretion permit to remain. However the order or decision of the Court (if any) in any such proceedings shall be announced in public. 7. Where the Court imposes one or more of the conditions specified in section 90(1) of the Act on the release on bail of a child, such condition shall be endorsed on the recognisance.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'What must the judge do when an accused child is charged with an indictable offence that the court can deal with summarily?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["The judge must release the accused child without trial unless new evidence is presented within 24 hours.","The judge must automatically sentence the child based on the severity of the offence without offering any rights or consent.","The judge must immediately transfer the case to a higher court without informing the child of any rights.","The judge must inform the accused child of their right to be tried by a jury and if the child consents, and the case is not one of an offence required to be tried by the Central Criminal Court or manslaughter, the court may take the child''s plea and try them summarily."],"justification":"the judge shall inform the accused child of his or her right to be tried by a jury and if the accused child (inquiry having been made of him or her by the judge) consents to the case being tried summarily, and, the case is not one of an offence which is required to be tried by the Central Criminal Court or manslaughter and the court is of opinion that the offence constitutes a minor offence fit to be tried summarily (or, where the child, having had the opportunity to have the assistance of his or her parent or guardian, adult spouse, an adult relative accompanying him or her, wishes to plead guilty, to be dealt with summarily), the court, having taken account of the age and level of maturity of the child concerned and any other facts that it considers relevant, may take the accused child’s plea and try him or her summarily."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '8. Where an accused child is before the court charged with an indictable offence with which the court has jurisdiction to deal summarily if the accused does not object, the judge shall inform the accused child of his or her right to be tried by a jury and if the accused child (inquiry having been made of him or her by the judge) consents to the case being tried summarily, and, the case is not one of an offence which is required to be tried by the Central Criminal Court or manslaughter and the court is of opinion that the offence constitutes a minor offence fit to be tried summarily (or, where the child, having had the opportunity to have the assistance of his or her parent or guardian, adult spouse, an adult relative accompanying him or her, wishes to plead guilty, to be dealt with summarily), the court, having taken account of the age and level of maturity of the child concerned and any other facts that it considers relevant, may take the accused child’s plea and try him or her summarily. 9. Where an accused child is before the court charged with an offence which is required to be tried by the Central Criminal Court or with manslaughter and wishes to plead guilty and the Court is satisfied that he or she understands the nature of the offence and the facts alleged, then, if the accused child signs a plea of guilty the judge may by order (Form [37.16](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/50df8d58-756c-4a67-9fb1-24829fc26ddb/Order Sending Forward On A Plea Of Guilty - Children Act, 2001, section 75(5) No. 37.16.docx/docx/1) Schedule and with the consent of the Director of Public Prosecutions (which consent may be conveyed as provided in rule 4 of [Order 24]([f669d9a7-009d-4d83-ddaa-000000000002|lng:en]59D3A380-82AD-48F7-9B9E-F3A4D928E077?url Order-24-District-Proceedings-Relating-to-Indictable-Offences)), or, where appropriate, of the Attorney-General, send him or her forward for sentence with that plea to the court to which, if he or she had pleaded not guilty, the accused could lawfully have been sent forward for trial.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'What happens if a child fails to comply with a community sanction order?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["The child is immediately sent to a juvenile detention center without any prior notice.","A summons is issued to the child to appear in court, and if the child does not appear, a warrant for arrest may be issued.","The community sanction order is automatically extended for an additional year.","The parents are fined an amount equivalent to the cost of the community service."],"justification":"Where it appears to the court, on application in that behalf by a member of the Garda Síochána that a child has failed, without reasonable cause, to comply with an order in force imposing a community sanction or any condition to which such order is subject, there shall be issued a summons to the child to appear before it in the Form [37.19](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/0c5e95d9-c34f-49b4-9498-59e297190d41/Summons To Appear To Answer Non-Compliance With Order Imposing Community Sanction - Children Act, 2001, section 136 No. 37.19.docx/docx/1), Schedule Unless the Court has excused the parents and/or guardian of the child from appearing, pursuant to section 90(5) of the Act, such summons to appear shall also be addressed to the parents and/or guardian of the child. If the child shall fail to appear in answer to said summons, the Court may issue a warrant in the Form [37.20](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/7ca36544-2c76-4b52-b872-c53cfc4c7efa/Warrant To Arrest - Children Act, 2001, section 136(3) No. 37.20.docx/docx/1), Schedule for his or her arrest."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '10. An order imposing a community sanction shall be in the Form [37.17](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/8035ee5b-1858-4077-96bd-a020c0eca283/Order For Community Sanction – Restriction On Movement Order - Children Act, 2001, Section 133 No. 37.17.docx/docx/1), Schedule Any application made under section 136 of the Act shall be preceded by the issue and service, at least four days before the date upon which the application is to be heard, on the accused, the parents or guardian of the accused, and any other person directly affected by the order, of a notice in the Form [37.18](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/49228326-5c3c-4883-9e3f-8389fa8bbbbc/Notice Of Application For An Order On Failure To Comply With Community Sanction – Restriction On Movement Order - Children Act, 2001, section 136 No. 37.18.docx/docx/1), Schedule 11. Where it appears to the court, on application in that behalf by a member of the Garda Síochána that a child has failed, without reasonable cause, to comply with an order in force imposing a community sanction or any condition to which such order is subject, there shall be issued a summons to the child to appear before it in the Form [37.19](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/0c5e95d9-c34f-49b4-9498-59e297190d41/Summons To Appear To Answer Non-Compliance With Order Imposing Community Sanction - Children Act, 2001, section 136 No. 37.19.docx/docx/1), Schedule Unless the Court has excused the parents and/or guardian of the child from appearing, pursuant to section 90(5) of the Act, such summons to appear shall also be addressed to the parents and/or guardian of the child. If the child shall fail to appear in answer to said summons, the Court may issue a warrant in the Form [37.20](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/7ca36544-2c76-4b52-b872-c53cfc4c7efa/Warrant To Arrest - Children Act, 2001, section 136(3) No. 37.20.docx/docx/1), Schedule for his or her arrest. The order of the Court on the hearing of the application shall be in the Form [37.21](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/2aacaa91-4e9f-40df-9245-5ba5a7d1c745/Order On Failure To Comply With Community Sanction – Restriction On Movement Order No. 37.21.docx/docx/1), Schedule'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'How much time before the hearing must the notice of application be served on the prosecuting Garda, the child, and the parent(s) or guardian of the child?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["not later than seven days","not later than fourteen days","not later than three days","not later than one day"],"justification":"Such application shall be preceded by the issue and service of a notice of application in the Form [37.29](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/e2e20bf3-0469-4cd1-98ea-a048bc6a6d6e/Notice Of Application For Resumption Of Proceedings - Children Act, 2001, section 83 No. 37.29.docx/docx/1), Schedule which shall be served not later than seven days before the date fixed for the hearing of such application on (a) the prosecuting Garda; the child and the parent(s) or guardian of the child or if the whereabouts of the parent(s) or guardian are unknown, on any adult relative of the child or other adult who has, under section 91(6) of the Act of 2001, accompanied the child during the proceedings"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '14. [4] An order of the Court pursuant to section or section 82(2)(a) of the Act in respect of an action plan ordering that the child concerned comply with it and be supervised by a probation and welfare officer while it is in operation shall be in the Form [37.28](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/e032dec5-d9bb-4e32-ab04-d37183aedfbc/Order Approving And Applying Action Plan - Children Act, 2001, section 82 No. 37.28.docx/docx/1) Schedule On such order being made, the proceedings shall be adjourned to a date fixed by the Court for review of compliance with the action plan in accordance with Section 84 of the Act. The probation and welfare officer who convened the relevant family conference shall be at liberty in such case to apply to the Court for the purposes of section 83 of the Act. Such application shall be preceded by the issue and service of a notice of application in the Form [37.29](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/e2e20bf3-0469-4cd1-98ea-a048bc6a6d6e/Notice Of Application For Resumption Of Proceedings - Children Act, 2001, section 83 No. 37.29.docx/docx/1), Schedule which shall be served not later than seven days before the date fixed for the hearing of such application on (a) the prosecuting Garda; the child and the parent(s) or guardian of the child or if the whereabouts of the parent(s) or guardian are unknown, on any adult relative of the child or other adult who has, under section 91(6) of the Act of 2001, accompanied the child during the proceedings'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'What form should be used when applying for an order authorising the taking of an intimate sample from a child?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Form 37.41","Form 37.40","Form 37.25","Form 41.37"],"justification":"An application for an order authorising the taking of an intimate sample from a child in the circumstances mentioned in section 17(1) of the Act of 2014 may be made to the Children Court by information on oath and in writing of the applicant in the Form [37.41](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/de32a3d5-2397-491a-a811-337bb5b9ef63/Information - Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014 (No. 11 of 2014) (the “Act of 2014”), section 17 - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008 (No. 7 of 2008) No. 37.41.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008 and the Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014* 15.[5] (1) In this rule: the “**Act of 2008**” means the [Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2008/act/7/enacted/en/html) (No. 7 of 2008); the “**Act of 2014**” means the [Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2014/act/11) (No. 11 of 2014); the expression “**intimate sample**” has the same meaning as in section 2(1) of the Act of 2014. (2) An application for an order authorising the taking of an intimate sample from a child in the circumstances mentioned in section 17(1) of the Act of 2014 may be made to the Children Court by information on oath and in writing of the applicant in the Form [37.41](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/de32a3d5-2397-491a-a811-337bb5b9ef63/Information - Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014 (No. 11 of 2014) (the “Act of 2014”), section 17 - Criminal Justice (Mutual Assistance) Act 2008 (No. 7 of 2008) No. 37.41.docx/docx/1), Schedule (3) Where the person to whom the application relates is a child (including a child who is a protected person), an application for any other order under the Act of 2014, for an order under section of the Act of 2008 (inserted by section 134 of the Act of 2014) or for an order under section 50A(6) of the International Criminal Court Act 2006 (inserted by section 140 of the Act of 2014) may be made to the Children Court by information on oath and in writing of the applicant in the Form [31.12](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/a4ab50b2-9cf8-40f8-be9e-aa7b45de32d4/Information - Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014 (No. 11 of 2014) (the “Act of 2014”) No. 31.12.docx/docx/1), Schedule with the necessary modifications, and the procedure set out in Order 31 shall apply, with such modifications as are necessary. (4) An information sworn for the purposes of section 17(1) of the Act of 2014 shall include details of (as the case may be): - the facts grounding the matters mentioned in section 17(4)(a) to of the Act of 2014;'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 37 - Proceedings Involving Children Or Young Persons', 'Court Rules', 'What form should a warrant issued on foot of an application under section 17(7) of the Act of 2014 take?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["The warrant should be in the Form 37.24, Schedule A.","The warrant should be in the Form 37.42, Schedule","The warrant should be in the Form 37.43, Schedule","The warrant should be in the Form 38.42, Schedule"],"justification":"a warrant issued on foot of such application shall be in the Form 37.42, Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '- the facts which establish that one of the conditions specified in section 17(1) of the Act of 2014 is satisfied, and - (iii) the means by which and time at which, the child concerned and any parent or guardian of that child (other than a parent or guardian to whom section 15(2) of the Act of 2014 applies), was informed of the intention to make the application (including the time and place at which it was intended to make the application), and - the rank of the applicant. (5) Any application under section 17(3) of the Act of 2014 may be made viva voce at the hearing and shall be determined before consideration of the application under section 17(1) of the Act of 2014. (6) Any application under section 17(7) of the Act of 2014 may be made viva voce at the hearing of the application under section 17(1) of the Act of 2014 and a warrant issued on foot of such application shall be in the Form 37.42, Schedule (7) Where the Court considers it necessary, it may adjourn the hearing of the application and direct a further notification to a parent or guardian of the child concerned. (8) Where the person to whom the appeal relates is a child (including a child who is a protected person), an appeal under section 81(11) or section 83(9) of the Act of 2014 may be made to the Children Court by notice of appeal in the Form [31.1A](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/cb54cac8-f457-4df9-bad9-76e32625da5f/Notice of Appeal against an Authorisation - Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014, section 81(11) No. 31.1A.docx/docx/1) or [31.1B](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/2831d9a5-1e62-4ad5-a400-19486fc9ce2a/Notice of appeal against a determination - Criminal Justice (Forensic Evidence and DNA Database System) Act 2014, section 83(9) No. 31.1B.docx/docx/1), Schedule as appropriate, with the necessary modifications, and the procedure set out in Order 31 shall apply, with such modifications as are necessary.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'In which court does this order apply?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["Supreme Court","District Court","County Court","Appellate Court"],"justification":"- Court: District"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '# Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters - Court: District # **Order 38: Miscellaneous Matters******[1]****'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What does this section cover?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["It discusses the jurisdiction of the court over international disputes.","It covers the legislative process in creating new laws.","It covers the power of the court in cases involving variances, defects, omissions, no offence disclosed, or no appearance.","It addresses the enforcement procedures by local law enforcement agencies."],"justification":"***Power of Court in cases of variance, defects, omissions, no offence disclosed or no appearance***"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## ***Power of Court in cases of variance, defects, omissions, no offence disclosed or no appearance***'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What is not considered material in cases of summary jurisdiction regarding the place of the offence?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["Any variance between the complaint and the evidence as to the place of the offence is deemed material, even if the offence was committed outside the jurisdiction of the judge hearing the case.","Variance between the complaint and the evidence as to the place of the offence is only deemed immaterial if the accused has never resided within the jurisdiction of the judge hearing the case.","The place of the offence is always deemed material regardless of where the accused was arrested or resides.","No variance between the complaint and the evidence as to the place of the offence is deemed material if the offence was committed within the jurisdiction of the judge hearing the case or the accused resides or was arrested within such jurisdiction."],"justification":"nor shall any variance between the complaint and the evidence adduced in support thereof, as to the place in which the offence or cause of complaint is stated to have been committed or to have arisen, be deemed material, provided that the said offence or cause of complaint was committed or arose within the jurisdiction of the Judge by whom the case is being heard, or that, the accused resides or in the case of an offence was arrested within such jurisdiction."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### **Variance between evidence and complaint** 1.(1) Subject to the provisions of paragraph (3), in cases of summary jurisdiction no variance between the complaint and the evidence adduced in support thereof, as to the time at which the offence or cause of complaint is stated to have been committed or to have arisen, shall be deemed material, provided that such information or complaint was in fact made within the time limited by law for making the same; nor shall any variance between the complaint and the evidence adduced in support thereof, as to the place in which the offence or cause of complaint is stated to have been committed or to have arisen, be deemed material, provided that the said offence or cause of complaint was committed or arose within the jurisdiction of the Judge by whom the case is being heard, or that, the accused resides or in the case of an offence was arrested within such jurisdiction. In any such case the Court may amend the summons, warrant or other document by which the proceedings were originated and proceed to hear and determine the matter.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What action can the court take regarding defects in documents?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["The court may require all parties to start the process over from the beginning.","The court may amend the documents or proceed as if no defect existed.","The court may fine the parties involved for any defects in the documents.","The court may ignore all defects and declare the documents invalid."],"justification":"the Court may amend any such summons, warrant or other document, or proceed in the matter as though no such defect, omission or variance had existed"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Defects* (2) Subject to the provisions of paragraph (3), no objection shall be taken or allowed on the ground of a defect in substance or in form or an omission in the summons, warrant or other document by which the proceedings were originated, or of any variance between any such document and the evidence adduced on the part of the prosecutor at the hearing of the case in summary proceedings or in proceedings in the Court relating to an indictable offence, but the Court may amend any such summons, warrant or other document, or proceed in the matter as though no such defect, omission or variance had existed.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What action can the court take if it decides to make an amendment?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["The court may impose a fine on all parties involved in the proceedings.","The court may extend the duration of the trial indefinitely without providing reasons.","The court may decide to merge the current case with another unrelated case.","The court may adjourn the proceedings to any future day at the same time or at any other place."],"justification":"it may upon such terms as it thinks fit adjourn the proceedings to any future day at the same time or at any other place."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Court’s discretion* (3) Provided, however, that if in the opinion of the Court the variance, defect or omission is one which has misled or prejudiced the accused or which might affect the merits of the case, it may refuse to make any such amendment and may dismiss the complaint either without prejudice to its being again made, or on the merits, as the Court thinks fit; or if it makes such amendment, it may upon such terms as it thinks fit adjourn the proceedings to any future day at the same time or at any other place.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'Under what circumstances can the court strike out a complaint?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["If the court is of opinion that the complaint discloses no offence at law, or if neither the prosecutor nor accused appears.","If the complainant refuses to pay the court fees.","If the complaint is written in a language other than the official language of the court.","If the complaint is submitted after the statutory time limit has expired."],"justification":"Where the Court is of opinion that the complaint before it discloses no offence at law, or if neither the prosecutor nor accused appears"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *No offence disclosed / No appearance* (4) Where the Court is of opinion that the complaint before it discloses no offence at law, or if neither the prosecutor nor accused appears, it may if it or thinks fit strike out the complaint with or without awarding costs.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this order?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["Order to freeze all bank accounts","Order to inspect and copy entries in Banker''s Books","Order to audit corporate financial statements","Order to liquidate assets of a bankrupt company"],"justification":"**Order to inspect and copy entries in Banker''s Books**"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## **Order to inspect and copy entries in Banker''s Books**'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What does an application under section 7 of the Bankers'' Books Evidence Act 1879 allow a party to do?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Inspect and take copies of entries in a banker''s books for any of the purposes of such proceedings.","Permit a party to demand and receive financial compensation from the bank for alleged discrepancies in their accounts.","Allow a party to modify entries in a banker''s books for the purpose of updating records.","Enable a party to seize and remove original documents from a banker''s books as evidence in court proceedings."],"justification":"authorising that party to inspect and take copies of entries in a banker''s books for any of the purposes of such proceedings"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Application for - venue* 2.(1) An application by a party to proceedings before the Court for an order under section 7 of the [Bankers'' Books Evidence Act 1879](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1879/act/11/enacted/en/print.html) (42 & 43 Vict. 11) authorising that party to inspect and take copies of entries in a banker''s books for any of the purposes of such proceedings may be made at any sitting of the Court for the Court district wherein the proceedings have been brought.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'When should the notice be lodged with the Clerk?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["Simultaneously with the making of the application","Prior to the making of the application","Within three days after the application is made","After the application has been made and approved"],"justification":"which shall be lodged with the Clerk prior to the making of the application"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- notice of* (2) Such application shall be preceded by the issue of a notice in the Form [38.1](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/28dec6c1-bed1-461d-aa0f-b8ffc8fb4a07/Notice Of Application For An Order To Inspect And Copy Entries In Books - Bankers'' Books Evidence Act, 1879 section 7 No. 38.1.docx/docx/1), Schedule which shall be lodged with the Clerk prior to the making of the application.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What form should the order of the Court granting the application take?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["Form [40.2], Schedule","Form [38.2], Schedule","Form [39.1], Schedule A","Form [38.3], Schedule"],"justification":"The order of the Court granting the application shall be in the Form [38.2], Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *Order of court* (3) The order of the Court granting the application shall be in the Form [38.2](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/0a875f41-bd60-4d54-9c31-cda7954ff181/Order To Inspect And Copy Entries In Books - Bankers'' Books Evidence Act, 1879 section 7 No. 38.2.docx/docx/1), Schedule which shall, unless the Court otherwise directs, be served upon the relevant bank three clear days before the order is to be obeyed. Service may be effected by delivering a copy of the order to the office of the bank wherein the relevant records are kept.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'Where can an application under Section 7A of the Bankers'' Books Evidence Act 1879 be made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["In any court within the jurisdiction where the bank is headquartered, irrespective of the location of the offence.","At any sitting of the High Court only, regardless of the location of the alleged offence.","At a special virtual sitting arranged exclusively for cases under Section 7A, irrespective of the location of the offence.","At any sitting of the Court for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged to have been committed."],"justification":"may be made at any sitting of the Court for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged to have been committed"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *Section 7A application- venue* (4) An application to the Court by a member of the Garda Síochána not below the rank of Superintendent under the provisions of section 7A of the [Bankers'' Books Evidence Act 1879](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1879/act/11/enacted/en/print.html) (42 & 43 Vict. as inserted by section 131 [Central Bank Act 1989](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1989/act/16/enacted/en/html), and as amended by section 14 of the [Disclosure of Certain Information for Taxation and Other Purposes Act 1996](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1996/act/25/enacted/en/html), may be made at any sitting of the Court for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged to have been committed and may be heard otherwise than in public.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What form should precede an application?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Form 38.01","Form 40.10","Form 38.10","Form 28.10"],"justification":"notice in the Form [38.10](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/626ef0ec-5ccd-4a40-974a-f6cc1834ac21/Notice Of Application For An Order To Inspect And Take Copies Of Entries In Books - Bankers’ Books Evidence Act, 1979 section 7 No. 38.10.docx/docx/1)"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- Notice of* (5) application shall be preceded by the issue of a notice in the Form [38.10](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/626ef0ec-5ccd-4a40-974a-f6cc1834ac21/Notice Of Application For An Order To Inspect And Take Copies Of Entries In Books - Bankers’ Books Evidence Act, 1979 section 7 No. 38.10.docx/docx/1), Schedule which shall be lodged with the Clerk prior to the making of the application.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of the section?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Procedure under Taxes Consolidation Act 1997","Procedure under Tax Reform Act 2000","Procedure under Income Tax Consolidation Act 1998","Procedure under Revenue Act 1995"],"justification":"Procedure under Taxes Consolidation Act 1997"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### **Procedure under Taxes Consolidation Act 1997**'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'Where should an application under Section 908A be made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["To the Secretary of the Ministry of Justice, regardless of the location of the offence or the financial institution.","To the Judge for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged is being, has been or is about to be committed or where the financial institution in respect of which the order is sought is located.","To the Minister responsible for the portfolio of law enforcement, irrespective of the specific jurisdiction or financial institution''s location.","To the nearest police station where the offence in question is alleged to have occurred."],"justification":"to the Judge for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged is being, has been or is about to be committed or where the financial institution in respect of which the order is sought is located"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *Section 908A application- venue* (7) An application by an authorised officer of the Revenue Commissioners under the provisions of section 908A of the [Taxes Consolidation Act 1997](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1997/act/39/enacted/en/html), as inserted by section 207 of the [Finance Act 1999](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1999/act/2/enacted/en/html), and as amended by section 68 of the [Finance Act 2000](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2000/act/3/enacted/en/html) and by section 132 of the [Finance Act 2002](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2002/act/5/enacted/en/html) shall be by information on oath and in writing, in the Form [38.12](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/f445692b-51bf-420d-bf63-4f233f110f3e/Information In Support Of Application For Order To Inspect And Take Copies Of Entries In Books Or Records - Taxes Consolidation Act, 1997 section 908a Amended No. 38.12.docx/docx/1), Schedule to the Judge for the Court district wherein the offence in question is alleged is being, has been or is about to be committed or where the financial institution in respect of which the order is sought is located, and may be heard otherwise than in public.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What does the Clerk do after criminal proceedings related to a death?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["The Clerk files the case documents in the courthouse archives.","The Clerk provides the next of kin with the verdict of the trial.","The Clerk updates the local newspaper with details of the proceedings.","The Clerk informs the coroner about the result of the proceedings."],"justification":"At the conclusion of criminal proceedings in the Court in relation to the death of a person the Clerk shall, pursuant to section 25(3) of the [Coroners Act 1962](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1962/act/9) (No. 9 of 1962), inform (in the Form [38.3](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/b809481e-be19-47cf-ad38-22b1c14ae8ac/Notice To Coroner - Coroners Act, 1962 section 25 (3) No. 38.3.docx/docx/1), Schedule the coroner holding an inquest in relation to the death of the result of the proceedings."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Notice under 1962 Act* 3. At the conclusion of criminal proceedings in the Court in relation to the death of a person the Clerk shall, pursuant to section 25(3) of the [Coroners Act 1962](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1962/act/9) (No. 9 of 1962), inform (in the Form [38.3](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/b809481e-be19-47cf-ad38-22b1c14ae8ac/Notice To Coroner - Coroners Act, 1962 section 25 (3) No. 38.3.docx/docx/1), Schedule the coroner holding an inquest in relation to the death of the result of the proceedings.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'Under which Act is the detention of cash regulated?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["Terrorism Act 2000","Criminal Justice Act 1994 (as amended)","Money Laundering Regulations 2017","Economic Crime (Transparency and Enforcement) Act 2022"],"justification":"Criminal Justice Act 1994 (as amended)"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## **Detention of Cash under section 38 of the Criminal Justice Act 1994 (as amended)**'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'What does ''the 1994 Act'' refer to?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["The Criminal Justice Act 1994, as amended by section 20 of the Proceeds of Crime (Amendment) Act 2005","The Education Reform Act 1994","The Data Protection Act 1994","The Human Rights Act 1994"],"justification":"“**the 1994 Act**” means the [Criminal Justice Act 1994](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1994/act/15), as amended by section 20 of the [Proceeds of Crime (Amendment) Act 2005](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2005/act/1/enacted/en/html)."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Interpretation – rules 5 to 8* 4. In rules 5 to 8 inclusive following, “**the 1994 Act**” means the [Criminal Justice Act 1994](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/1994/act/15), as amended by section 20 of the [Proceeds of Crime (Amendment) Act 2005](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2005/act/1/enacted/en/html).'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 38 - Miscellaneous Matters', 'Court Rules', 'To whom should the application for the detention of cash be directed?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["To a Judge of the Court assigned to the Court district wherein the cash was seized.","To a police officer in charge of the precinct where the cash was seized.","To the prosecutor handling the case related to the seizure of the cash.","To the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court."],"justification":"Such application shall be made to a Judge of the Court assigned to the Court district wherein the cash was seized."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '### *Application for order authorising detention of cash* 5.(1) An application to the Court by a member of the Garda Síochána or an officer of Customs and Excise under section 38(2) of the 1994 Act for an order authorising the detention beyond 48 hours of cash seized by virtue of section 38 of the 1994 Act shall be made by the information on oath and in writing of the applicant, in the Form [38.4](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/05cc38a8-2b3b-4ee5-a373-05698fc20c95/Information - Criminal Justice Act 1994, section 38 (as amended by section 20, Proceeds of Crime (Amendment) Act 2005) No. 38.4.docx/docx/1), Schedule Such application shall be made to a Judge of the Court assigned to the Court district wherein the cash was seized. Where the Judge is satisfied that the urgency of the case so requires, such application may be heard and determined on the evidence viva voce and on oath of the applicant. In such case, a written note of the evidence given shall be prepared by the applicant and signed by the Judge.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 102 - Cases Stated', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this section?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["*When case is ignored entirely*","*When case stated with request*","*Where facts are not stated*","*Where case stated without request*"],"justification":"*Where case stated without request*"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *Where case stated without request*'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 12 - Miscellaneous Provisions', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this section?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":0,"options":["Schedules and Forms","Staff Training","Contracts and Agreements","Policies and Procedures"],"justification":"**3 - Schedules and Forms**"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## **3 - Schedules and Forms**'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 12A - Funds In Court', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this order?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Order - Funds on Hold","Order - Funds in Custody","Order 12A - Funds In Court","Order - Funds Under Review"],"justification":"# Order 12A - Funds In Court"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '# Order 12A - Funds In Court - Court: District # **Order 12A: Funds in Court******[1]****'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 23 - Trial Of Summary Offences', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this section?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":3,"options":["PENALTIES","INTRODUCTION","PROCEDURES","III. FINES"],"justification":"## III. FINES"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## III. FINES'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 27 - Estreatment Of Recognisances Forfeiture Of Money Lodged', 'Court Rules', 'What is the title of this section?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":1,"options":["*Maintenance of order*","*Enforcement of order*","*Enforcement of law*","*Implementation of rules*"],"justification":"*Enforcement of order*"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## *Enforcement of order*'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'Under which act does this section operate?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["Firearms Act, 1968","Criminal Justice Act, 1988","Firearms and Offensive Weapons Act, 1990","Offensive Weapons Act, 2015"],"justification":"under the Firearms and Offensive Weapons Act, 1990"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '## - under the Firearms and Offensive Weapons Act, 1990'),
