                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'How is the application for a search warrant made?', 'mcq', '{"correct_index":2,"options":["By filing a motion for discovery with the court, detailing the need for evidence collection.","By providing a detailed affidavit in any standard legal form, not specifically Form 34.11.","By the information on oath and in writing in Form 34.11, Schedule","By submitting a verbal request to a judge during an oral hearing."],"justification":"Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing in the Form [34.11](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/796bb4a0-5bbb-45ec-9514-4a6be944cf2f/Information For Search Warrant - Firearms And Offensive Weapons Act, 1990 - section 15 No. 34.11.docx/docx/1), Schedule"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- by sworn information.* (2) Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing in the Form [34.11](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/796bb4a0-5bbb-45ec-9514-4a6be944cf2f/Information For Search Warrant - Firearms And Offensive Weapons Act, 1990 - section 15 No. 34.11.docx/docx/1), Schedule of the member of the Garda Síochána seeking the issue of the warrant.'),
